---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Water Heater Install & Repair | Berkeley Plumbing — Newbury Park, CA"
  description="Water heater installation and repair in Newbury Park and the Conejo Valley. Tankless and traditional systems. C-36 licensed, upfront pricing. CSLB #1115151."
>

  <!-- Page hero -->
  <section class="bg-navy-900 text-white py-16 lg:py-24 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <a href="/" class="text-copper text-sm hover:text-copper-light mb-6 inline-block">← Back to home</a>
      <p class="text-copper font-semibold text-sm uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">Services</p>
      <h1 class="font-display text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold mb-5">Water Heater Installation and Repair</h1>
      <p class="text-slate-300 text-lg lg:text-xl leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
        Tankless and traditional water heater installation, replacement, and repair in the Conejo Valley. Upfront pricing before any work begins.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Content -->
  <section class="py-16 lg:py-20 px-4 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-12">

      <div class="lg:col-span-2 prose prose-slate max-w-none">

        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-navy-900">Tankless Water Heaters</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
          Tankless (on-demand) water heaters are a common upgrade for homes in the Conejo Valley, especially during ADU builds or kitchen and bathroom remodels where space is at a premium. They heat water only when needed, which reduces energy use and eliminates the standby heat loss of a tank system.
        </p>
        <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
          Proper sizing is critical. An undersized unit won't keep up with simultaneous demand across multiple fixtures. I'll size the unit to match your household's actual usage, not just the minimum spec.
        </p>

        <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-navy-900 mt-6">Tankless Services</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-slate-600">
          <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-copper mt-1 flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">✓</span> New installation: gas and electric tankless systems</li>
          <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-copper mt-1 flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">✓</span> Conversion from tank to tankless</li>
          <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-copper mt-1 flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">✓</span> Recirculation pump installation for instant hot water</li>
          <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-copper mt-1 flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">✓</span> Descaling and maintenance</li>
          <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-copper mt-1 flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">✓</span> Repair and component replacement</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-navy-900 mt-8">Traditional Tank Water Heaters</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
          Standard tank water heaters remain the most cost-effective option for most homes. When a tank reaches the end of its life, a straightforward replacement with a properly-sized unit is often the right call.
        </p>

        <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-navy-900 mt-6">Tank Services</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-slate-600">
          <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-copper mt-1 flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">✓</span> Tank replacement (gas and electric)</li>
          <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-copper mt-1 flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">✓</span> Expansion tank installation (required by California code in closed systems)</li>
          <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-copper mt-1 flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">✓</span> T&P valve and anode rod service</li>
          <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-copper mt-1 flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">✓</span> Leak repair and drain valve replacement</li>
          <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-copper mt-1 flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">✓</span> Seismic strapping (California requirement)</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="mt-8 bg-copper/5 border border-copper/20 rounded-lg p-5">
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
            <strong class="text-navy-900">California note:</strong> Water heater installations in California require a permit in most jurisdictions. Berkeley Plumbing handles permit coordination and ensures all work meets current California Plumbing Code, including seismic bracing requirements.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Sidebar -->
      <div class="lg:col-span-1">
        <div class="bg-stone-warm rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-100 sticky top-24">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-navy-900 mb-4">Request an Estimate</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-5 leading-relaxed">
            Know the cost before any work begins. Upfront pricing, always.
          </p>
          <a
            href="/contact/"
            class="block w-full bg-copper hover:bg-copper-light text-white font-semibold py-3 px-5 rounded text-center transition-colors mb-3"
          >
            Get an Estimate
          </a>
          <a
            href="tel:(310) 733-7808"
            class="block w-full border border-slate-300 hover:border-navy-800 text-slate-700 font-semibold py-3 px-5 rounded text-center transition-colors text-sm"
          >
            Call (310) 733-7808
          </a>
          <div class="mt-6 pt-6 border-t border-slate-200 space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
            <p class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-copper" aria-hidden="true">✓</span> Gas and electric systems</p>
            <p class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-copper" aria-hidden="true">✓</span> Tankless specialists</p>
            <p class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-copper" aria-hidden="true">✓</span> Permit coordination</p>
            <p class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-copper" aria-hidden="true">✓</span> CSLB #1115151</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Service areas -->
  <section class="py-12 px-4 bg-stone-warm border-t border-slate-100">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm text-center">
        Water heater service in:
        <a href="/service-areas/newbury-park/" class="text-copper hover:underline">Newbury Park</a>,
        <a href="/service-areas/agoura-hills/" class="text-copper hover:underline">Agoura Hills</a>,
        <a href="/service-areas/thousand-oaks/" class="text-copper hover:underline">Thousand Oaks</a>,
        <a href="/service-areas/westlake-village/" class="text-copper hover:underline">Westlake Village</a>, and
        <a href="/service-areas/calabasas/" class="text-copper hover:underline">Calabasas</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
